problem_text:
Let G be a finite simple group of Lie type defined over a field of characteristic p, and V an absolutely irreducible G-module over a field of the same characteristic. Is it true that in the following cases the split extension of V by G must contain an element whose order is distinct from the order of any element of G?
a) G = U4(q);
b) G = S2n(q), n ⩾3;
c) G = O2n+1(q), n ⩾3;
d) G = O+ 2n(q), n ⩾4;
e) G = O− 2n(q), n ⩾4;
f) G = 3D4(q), q ̸= 2;
g) G = E6(q);
h) G = 2E6(q);
i) G = E7(q);
j) G = G2(2m).
V. D. Mazurov
